From: tawc
Origin: own

Cross-build the gfxstream host renderer (libgfxstream_backend.so) for
Android NDK. Upstream's meson build only knows linux/darwin/windows/qnx
host platforms — Android is built via Soong inside AOSP and isn't
reachable from a standalone NDK toolchain. We need it from outside AOSP
for the gfxstream-bridge GPU path (notes/gfxstream-bridge.md), where a
kumquat server inside the Tawc compositor app forwards Vulkan command
streams from the chroot to the device's vendor blob via gfxstream's
EGL-on-EGL + dlopen("libvulkan.so") backend.

Changes:

  meson.build:
    - Add an 'android' branch alongside 'linux' (UNSTABLE_VULKAN_*
      and threads).
    - Define -DANDROID=1 — NDK clang defines __ANDROID__ but not the
      bare ANDROID macro that egl_global_info.cpp / egl_os_api_egl.cpp /
      vk_android_native_buffer_gfxstream.h check for.
    - Don't add -DHAVE_MEMFD_CREATE on Android: NDK exposes the
      function only since API 30, and SharedMemory_posix.cpp's syscall
      fallback works on every kernel that ships with Android 11+ (the
      bridge's effective floor anyway).

  host/meson.build:
    - native_sub_window_android.cpp on Android (already in tree —
      wraps ANativeWindow_*).
    - VK_USE_PLATFORM_ANDROID_KHR instead of VK_USE_PLATFORM_XCB_KHR.
    - Link against -lnativewindow (AHardwareBuffer_*), -landroid
      (ANativeWindow_*), -llog (__android_log_print).

  host/decoder_common/meson.build,
  host/vulkan/{meson.build,cereal/meson.build,emulated_textures/meson.build}:
    - Skip X11Support.cpp; pick VK_USE_PLATFORM_ANDROID_KHR for
      android (mirrors the linux branches structurally).

  host/gl/glestranslator/egl/meson.build:
    - Document that Android only takes the EGL-on-EGL backend
      (egl_os_api_egl.cpp, always included). egl_global_info.cpp
      switches on `defined(ANDROID)`.

  host/gl/glestranslator/common/gl_dispatch.cpp:
    - Don't include <GL/glx.h> on android. NDK clang defines __linux__,
      and gfxstream's existing #ifdef __linux__ would otherwise pull
      GLX in.

  host/frame_buffer.h, host/native_sub_window.h:
    - Fix the case-mismatch include ("GlesCompat.h" → "gles_compat.h").
      The actual file is lowercase; the existing Linux host build
      doesn't notice because it always has GFXSTREAM_ENABLE_HOST_GLES
      defined and takes the alternate include.

  host/native_sub_window_stub.cpp:
    - Include <stdio.h> for stderr/fprintf.

  host/vulkan/vk_decoder_global_state.cpp:
    - Replace <vndk/hardware_buffer.h> (vendor-process only — not in
      NDK) with <android/hardware_buffer.h>. The translation unit only
      uses plain AHardwareBuffer*, so the NDK header covers it.

  third_party/meson.build:
    - Expose `inc_third_party_android` for android targets, used by
      the build script to surface cutils/native_handle.h (which the
      NDK doesn't ship; libcutils is part of AOSP). The build script
      copies just the cutils/ subtree into a shims dir and -I's that —
      it does NOT add the full third_party/android/include path
      because that would shadow the NDK's own android/* headers.

